  "texts": [
    "Our pipeline follows the retrieval-augmented generation framework of Lewis et al. (2020), which combines a retriever with a generative language model.",
    "The goal is to answer a natural language query q by grounding the language model's response in documents retrieved from a large corpus D.",
    "In the first step, a query encoder f q and a document encoder f d project queries and documents into a shared vector space (Karpukhin et al., 2020).",
    "During retrieval, the query representation f q (q) is compared to all document embeddings f d (d) using inner product similarity.",
    "Subsequently, we select the top-k most relevant documents:"
  ],
